			<sumFormula>Not applicable</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Iron and steel smelting is a process where metals are extracted from iron ore or other valuable waste resources. This is done according to the basic principles of physical chemistry, thermodynamics, kinetics, transmission principle, reaction engineering and metallurgy. The extracted metals are then refined and made into iron and steel materials with certain properties. The process involves heating the ore to high temperatures, a process known as smelting, to extract the base metal.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">铁和钢的冶炼是从铁矿石或其他有价值的废弃资源中提取金属的过程。这是根据物理化学、热力学、动力学、传输原理、反应工程和冶金学的基本原理进行的。然后，提取出的金属被精炼并制成具有一定性质的铁和钢材料。该过程涉及将矿石加热到高温，这个过程被称为冶炼，以提取基础金属。</common:generalComment>
